      • onEvent

        void onEvent(int time,
           int uid,
           java.lang.String interfaceName,
           java.lang.String method,
           java.util.List<java.lang.Object> params,
           java.lang.String[] paramTypes,
           long eventsCounter)
        Callback method that is triggered whenever a new system event has occurred.

        Implement your analysis HERE. Note that to receive events about an app, it must be traced via DroidTracerService.startTracingApp(int) or DroidTracerService.setLowestUidTraced(int). Events are also received about a service that has been whitelisted via DroidTracerService.addInterfaceToWhitelist(java.lang.String).

        Parameters:
        time - the Unix time stamp (seconds since 1970)
        uid - the Linux UID that uniquely identifies an app
        interfaceName - the IBinder interface name that identifies a service (e.g., com.android.internal.telephony.ISms), or "syscall" if the event ressambles an intercepted system call.
        method - the name of the method called (e.g., sendText() if SMS was sent), or system call function name (e.g., sys_open)
        params - the unmarshalled method arguments
        paramTypes - the Java types of method arguments
        eventsCounter - the accumulated number of events sent since loading of the kernel module
